WEBVTT

00:00.875 --> 00:02.627
NARRATOR: Previously
on Chesapeake Shores...

00:02.794 --> 00:05.839
- JESS: They're like any other family.
- They own a little of everything.

00:06.005 --> 00:09.300
You're wrong about Danielle, and
you have no idea how to apologize.

00:09.509 --> 00:13.847
- Weddings are all about family.
- We would love to renew our vows here.

00:14.055 --> 00:16.516
- NELL: Oh, bless you.
- I don't know how I feel.

00:16.725 --> 00:18.393
- There's something...
- Not right.

00:18.601 --> 00:21.479
- Yeah.
- David, you are the new CEO...

00:21.688 --> 00:24.482
- of Peck Enterprises.
- Are you kidding me?

00:24.983 --> 00:26.234
- TRACE: And kick.
- Ta-da.

00:26.401 --> 00:28.445
- Whoo!
- I'm not ready to say goodbye yet.

00:28.611 --> 00:30.822
Well, maybe we don't have to.

00:32.073 --> 00:33.199
[♪♪♪]

00:33.366 --> 00:35.660
BREE: Jess, we've been going
over this the entire day.

00:35.827 --> 00:38.290
They only asked David to
take over the business.

00:38.291 --> 00:39.331
He didn't actually accept.

00:39.497 --> 00:43.293
- Need a second opinion. I'm calling Abby.
- Wait, no. There's no reason to panic.

00:43.501 --> 00:46.671
Really? Anyone ever say, "Don't
panic," when there's no reason to...

00:46.838 --> 00:49.674
or say it when they're trying
to convince you there isn't?

00:49.841 --> 00:54.220
Yes. Wait, no. Just don't call
her, okay? She's on tour with Trace.

00:54.387 --> 00:56.514
We promised not to call
unless an emergency.

00:56.681 --> 01:00.018
Let's just be happy having my
soul crushed isn't an emergency.

01:00.226 --> 01:02.228
- I'm calling Abby.
- But she's on vacation.

01:02.395 --> 01:03.605
[JESS GASPS]

01:03.813 --> 01:05.065
- No!
- No.

01:05.230 --> 01:07.150
[♪♪♪]

01:07.358 --> 01:08.985
[CROWD CHEERING IN DISTANCE]

01:09.152 --> 01:10.278
Hello?

01:10.445 --> 01:11.946
Hello?

01:12.530 --> 01:14.574
- Who's that?
- It was Jess, but she hung up.

01:14.741 --> 01:19.412
- I wonder if I should call her back?
- If it's important, she'll call you back.

01:19.579 --> 01:21.831
Yeah. Yeah, you're probably right.

01:21.998 --> 01:25.668
Abs, you need to relax. Carrie
and Caitlyn are with Wes...

01:25.835 --> 01:28.713
your office said everything's
fine, and you're on tour.

01:28.922 --> 01:32.091
You're on tour, I'm just following
you, which makes me your...

01:32.258 --> 01:33.927
My bodyguard?

01:34.093 --> 01:36.179
- Your bodyguard?
- And as my bodyguard...

01:36.346 --> 01:38.848
your job is to stay very close to me.

01:39.015 --> 01:40.058
ABBY: Oh, really?

01:40.225 --> 01:41.810
- Heh, heh.
- How's this?

01:41.976 --> 01:43.770
Not close enough.

01:43.937 --> 01:46.105
Trace, we're on.

01:46.523 --> 01:48.108
Hey, Abby, you having fun?

01:48.274 --> 01:50.485
- Yeah.
- MAN [OVER PA]: Hello, Dallas.

01:50.693 --> 01:53.404
Opening tonight with a new
album that just went gold...

01:53.571 --> 01:55.949
here's Trace Riley and
the Trace Riley Band.

01:56.116 --> 01:57.408
Well, time to go to work.

01:57.742 --> 02:01.371
- Don't be late for dinner.
- I'll see you in 20. Heh, heh.

02:01.579 --> 02:02.872
[LAUGHS]

02:04.124 --> 02:07.335
Looking good, Dallas.
Thanks for coming out.

02:08.419 --> 02:09.920
One, two, three.

